SmallerMaker is a small bash script designed to compress images without sacrificing quality.
http://github.com/kristoferbaxter/SmallerMaker/

Required dependencies
---------------------
1. ImageMagick - http://www.imagemagick.org/
2. JpegTran - http://jpegclub.org/jpegtran/
3. wrjpgcom
4. jpegoptim - http://www.kokkonen.net/tjko/projects.html
5. Gifsicle - http://www.lcdf.org/gifsicle/
6. OptiPNG - http://optipng.sourceforge.net/
7. PNGOUT - http://advsys.net/ken/utils.htm#pngout 
   * Please note you must download PNGOUT from Ken Silverman's Utility Page.
8. ADVPNG - http://advancemame.sourceforge.net/comp-readme.html

Example usage
---------------------
1. SmallerMaker can accept a single file to compress ( will replace existing file )
   
   kbaxterlt:SmallerMaker kbaxter$ sh smallermaker.sh /Users/kbaxter/Desktop/test/test.gif
   
2. SmallerMaker can accept a single directory to compress all images within ( and all child folders too )

   kbaxterlt:SmallerMaker kbaxter$ sh smallermaker.sh /Users/kbaxter/Desktop/test


